  1. Using the initial dataset variable, use case_when() to create a new variable heavy_food which is equal to “heavy” when total calories are greater than 500, “low” when total calories are less than 250 and “average” for all other cases. Count the number of observations in each created category.

```r
heavy_food <- fastfood
heavy_food %>%
  mutate(heavy_food = case_when (calories > 500 ~ "heavy",
                                 calories < 250 ~ "low",
                                 T ~ "average"))

calories_type <- fastfood

  mutate(calories_type = cut_number(calories,n=3,labels = c("low","med","high")))%>%

  theme_linedraw()

23.Calculate and show the average (mean) total_fat for each type of restaurant. No need to save it as a variable.

fastfood %>% group_by(restaurant) %>%
  summarise(total_fat = mean(total_fat))
